{{Politics of Denmark}}
'''Parliamentary elections''' were held in [[Denmark]] on 8 December 1981.<ref name=DN>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] & StÃ¶ver, P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p525 ISBN 9873832956097</ref> The [[Social Democrats (Denmark)|Social Democratic Party]] remained the largest in the [[Folketing]], with 59 of the 179 seats. Voter turnout was 83.3% in Denmark proper, 55.4% in the [[Faroe Islands]] and 61.0% in [[Greenland]].<ref name=NS>Nohlen & StÃ¶ver, p545</ref>
